  "notes": "Phonological-awareness flashcard set: one card per Arabic letter (28 letters across pages 1-7; page 8 is an answer/label key strip). Each card shows the target letter plus 3 pictures; the child writes/identifies the target letter and decides which pictured word(s) contain its sound. Cards mix correct examples with distractors, so many items carry position 'none' (target sound absent). Word identities were cross-checked against the labeled Arabic key strip on p008 by sight. Some letters (ض, ظ, ك, ل etc.) had a blank picture cell in the card grid, so fewer than 3 picture-words appear for those. Vocabulary read by sight; common kid nouns. Several distractor mappings are inferred (which 3 pictures sit on which card) and could vary; the correct-example word per letter is high confidence, the distractor assignments are medium confidence. p008 dense answer strip Arabic labels partially small — used for confirmation, not all individually legible.",
